      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**Compliance Memorandum:**\n\n**Introduction:**\n\nOur organization is committed to maintaining the highest standards of Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Combating the Financing of Terrorism (CFT) regulations. This memorandum outlines our policies and procedures for ensuring the effective implementation of these regulations, as required by law.\n\n**Section 1: Customer Due Diligence (CDD)**\n\nWe are required to conduct thorough Customer Due Diligence (CDD) on all customers, including but not limited to, Politically Exposed Persons (PEPs), High-Risk Jurisdictions, and individuals from high-risk categories. This includes verifying the source of funds and source of wealth, and assessing the risk of money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\n**Section 2: Risk-Based Approach (RBA)**\n\nOur risk-based approach is a critical component of our AML/CFT program. We will assess the risk of money laundering and terrorist financing on a regular basis, and implement enhanced due diligence procedures as necessary.\n\n**Section 3: Enhanced Due Diligence (EDD)**\n\nWe will conduct enhanced due diligence on customers who are classified as High-Risk, or who have been identified as PEPs or have had adverse media checks",
